<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Thats some impressive numbers, even more impressive at level 40. You must have god weapons or something, my warrior at 36 with duel lams dont approach single hit damage in the 200 range at all. ANd even if I were to go with a higher damage weapon, still not close. Anyway, why run away? If you are soloing, that HG wont be snared and  will be hot on your ass at full speed. I suppose you can get a bow shot off every now and than, but honestly, as a warrior, I dont think you will accomplish much by running away. Not like you gonna heal yourself outside of bind wound or cast spells. If you hitting that hard regularly, you should be able to drop that HG fairly fast and regardless, your best bet is just to tank it. You regen a little HP as you run away I suppose, but do you think the little you regen will really matter? Dont think there is a thing such as warrior kiting since warriors cant really do damage to a mob without being in melee range, beyond bows, nor can they root a mob and heal themselves .</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
