<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I feel for you Krallek. It seems these people didn't hear one word you said besides "solo" and "damage". Especialy the first person to reply, saying something about lammy's not doing 200 damage - wonder which one of his friends bought him that account.<p>

Anyway, there's nothing wrong with soloing a warrior, but it only works efficiently if you have very good equipment. I started soloing my warrior in Overthere at about level 40 and went to level 47 in 2 weeks (and i wasn't playing constantly). I didn't have any regen items or anything, and the reason this worked was because I am an ogre and had sort of a lot of hps + being very twinked. I was able to kill a mob with about 1 bubble or less damage taken then go bandage and repeat. With maxed bandage after a while this was very fast and great exp - MUCH better than a group.<p>

In reply to the question no one seemed to address... It sounds like it would work some of the time, however just like you get a chance for your attack to recover, so does the giant. and so in order to solo like this you'd need to bandage which means you couldnt really take more than 2 bubs of damage killing it. I wouldnt suggest this method at all really, but an interesting tactic nonetheless. Weighted axes are cool for the first hit on a mob then quickly swap weapons.<p>

Good luck Krallek</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
